---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="GDPR | St Mary the Virgin, Henbury" description="GDPR information for St Mary the Virgin, Henbury website.">
  <section class="container-width mt-12">
    <article class="section-rule max-w-4xl">
      <p class="eyebrow">Data protection</p>
      <h1 class="mt-2 text-5xl">GDPR</h1>
      <p class="mt-4 text-nave-900">This page gives a simple summary of data protection and GDPR context for this website.</p>
      <p class="mt-3 text-nave-900"><strong>Who receives messages:</strong> Messages sent using the contact route are processed via Formspree.</p>
      <p class="mt-3 text-nave-900"><strong>What is collected:</strong> Name, email address, and message text.</p>
      <p class="mt-3 text-nave-900"><strong>Purpose:</strong> To respond to direct enquiries.</p>
      <p class="mt-3 text-nave-900"><strong>Retention:</strong> Data is retained only as long as needed for correspondence and basic records.</p>
      <p class="mt-3 text-nave-900"><strong>Your rights:</strong> You may request access, correction, or deletion of personal data.</p>
      <p class="mt-3 text-nave-900"><strong>Contact route:</strong> Use the <a href="/contact">Contact page</a> to make a request.</p>
      <p class="mt-3 text-nave-900"><strong>Related pages:</strong> <a href="/gdpr">GDPR</a> | <a href="/privacy">Privacy</a> | <a href="/terms">Terms</a>.</p>
      <p class="mt-3 text-nave-900">
        <strong>United Kingdom:</strong> <a href="https://www.legislation.gov.uk/eur/2016/679/contents" rel="noreferrer">UK GDPR text on legislation.gov.uk</a>
        and the <a href="https://www.legislation.gov.uk/ukpga/2018/12/contents" rel="noreferrer">Data Protection Act 2018 (UK)</a>.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-3 text-nave-900">
        <strong>Ireland:</strong> <a href="https://eur-lex.europa.eu/eli/reg/2016/679/oj/eng" rel="noreferrer">EU GDPR text on EUR-Lex</a>
        and the <a href="https://www.irishstatutebook.ie/eli/2018/act/7/enacted/en/html" rel="noreferrer">Data Protection Act 2018 (Ireland)</a>.
      </p>
    </article>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
